===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|rumour|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term/t|la|rūmor||common talk}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈɹuːmə(ɹ)/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈɹumɚ/}}
* {{rhymes|uːmə(r)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~|rumors}}

# {{context|countable|lang=en}} A [[statement]] or [[claim]] of [[questionable]] [[accuracy]], from no known [[reliable]] source, usually spread by [[word of mouth]].
#: ''There's a '''rumor''' going round that he's going to get married.''
# {{context|uncountable|lang=en}} [[information|Information]] or [[misinformation]] of the kind contained in such claims.
#: ''They say he used to be a thief, but that's just '''rumor'''.''

